---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="Tacky Turquoise refund and return policy. All sales final with one shipping-damage exception."
>
  <section class="policy">
    <div class="policy__inner">
      <div class="policy__crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; Refund Policy</div>

      <h1>Refund <em>Policy.</em></h1>
      <p class="policy__updated">Last updated: 4/25/2026</p>

      <p class="policy__lede">
        Every piece we sell is handmade and one-of-a-kind. <strong>All sales are final.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>The One Exception</h2>
      <p>If a piece arrives damaged from shipping, we'll make it right.</p>
      <p>To report a damaged shipment:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Email <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a> within 48 hours of delivery</li>
        <li>Include your order number (e.g., TC-1234)</li>
        <li>Include clear photos of the damaged piece and the packaging</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        We'll review the claim and respond within 2 business days. Damaged pieces must
        be returned to us before any refund is issued. We'll provide return shipping
        instructions when we approve the claim.
      </p>
      <p>
        Once we receive the returned piece, we'll process your refund to the original
        payment method within 5 business days. Depending on your bank, the refund may
        take an additional 5–10 business days to appear on your statement.
      </p>

      <h2>What Counts as Shipping Damage</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The piece arrived broken, cracked, or with stones missing</li>
        <li>The packaging shows clear damage from the shipping process</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Normal variations in handmade jewelry — slight differences in stone color, bead
        size, or finish — are not damage. Each piece is unique and the photos on the
        product page represent the actual piece you'll receive.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Don't Cover</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Damage from wear after delivery</li>
        <li>Pieces lost or damaged after delivery has been confirmed</li>
        <li>Returns for any reason other than shipping damage</li>
        <li>Pieces shipped to the wrong address because of incorrect information at checkout (always double-check your shipping address before placing an order)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Lost Packages</h2>
      <p>
        If your tracking shows the package was delivered but you didn't receive it,
        contact USPS first to file a claim. We're happy to help where we can, but once
        USPS marks a package as delivered, the package is in their and your custody,
        not ours.
      </p>

      <h2>Order Cancellations</h2>
      <p>
        You can request to cancel an order before it ships by emailing
        <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a> with
        your order number. If we haven't already purchased the shipping label, we can
        usually accommodate the cancellation and issue a full refund. Once a label has
        been purchased, the order is in motion and we generally can't cancel it.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For damaged-shipment claims or any questions:
        <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="policy__signoff">
        <strong>Apex Quality Analytics LLC</strong>
        DBA Tacky Turquoise<br />
        Olathe, Colorado
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Base>
